# Onboarding Checklist for New Developers

Welcome to the team! Follow this checklist to get set up and productive quickly.

---

## 1. Prerequisites
- Install .NET 8 SDK
- Install Docker Desktop
- Install Visual Studio Code (recommended) or Visual Studio
- Get access to Azure DevOps and Azure Portal

## 2. Clone the Repository
- `git clone <repo-url>`
- `cd Trello`

## 3. Configure Local Environment
- Copy `appsettings.Development.json` templates for each service and fill in local values
- Ensure no secrets are committed to source control

## 4. Run Services Locally
- Use Docker Compose: `docker-compose -f docker/docker-compose.yml up --build`
- Or run individual services: `dotnet run` in each service directory
- Access Swagger UI at `http://localhost:<port>/swagger`

## 5. Review Documentation
- Read all docs in `src/application/` for security, CI/CD, Docker, Bicep, and API practices
- Review `infra/` for Bicep templates and deployment scripts

## 6. Working with Azure
- Request access to required Azure resources (RBAC roles)
- Use managed identity and Key Vault for secrets

## 7. Making Changes
- Follow Git flow: branch, commit, PR, merge
- Write/update unit tests for new features
- Update documentation as needed

## 8. Troubleshooting
- See `TROUBLESHOOTING-FAQ.md` in this folder for common issues

---

**Welcome aboard! If you have questions, ask your onboarding buddy or the project maintainer.**


